description:
&lt;p&gt;The Microbiology Department at Pathology First is looking for an experienced Senior Biomedical Scientist to join their team as Team Manager. This is a great step up for a Specialist Biomedical Scientist into management. The post holder will be required to oversee and manage a team of Biomedical Scientists, as well as Junior and Support staff who perform analyses and processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The main responsibilities of the role are outlined below:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure high quality analysis, agreed quality standards of service delivery and key performance indicators.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide professional knowledge and leadership skills to Specialist Biomedical Scientists, Trainees, BMS and pathology support staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide expert technical advice to clinicians as to the appropriateness of tests, timescales and scientific guidance as required. To both Hub and Essential service laboratory teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have expert analytical and technical knowledge to perform and manage specialist analytical procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with all policies as required by regulatory directives, accreditation bodies and local management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications and experience required:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HCPC State Registration as a Biomedical Scientist, with continued CPD&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Completion of a specialist portfolio in Microbiology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Management Qualification to ILM level 3 or relevant experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MSc /FIBMS (by examination)/ IBMS Higher Specialist Diploma and is currently in possession of Fellowship Class of the IBMS or equivalent experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High level working knowledge of Microbiology techniques and practices at post honours degree level&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert interpretive and diagnostic skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work across 3 different sites in a 24-7 work environment if and when required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
